definitions.definition: ( Greek mythology ) The goddess of wisdom , especially strategic warfare, the arts, and especially crafts, in particular, weaving ; daughter of Zeus and Metis . Her Roman counterpart is Minerva .
A city in Umatilla County , Oregon , United States .
A female given name from Ancient Greek .
